description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 5 Staff Nurse Haematology and Oncology Daycare Unit&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;37.5 hours per week&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Are you a children’s nurse wishing to develop your skills in paediatric haematology, oncology and bone marrow transplantation? Do you want to be part of a focused, forward thinking, and dynamic multi-disciplinary team working in a dedicated children’s hospital?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for highly motivated and enthusiastic Children’s Nurse to join our team. The unit comprises an 14 bedded in patient facility, 9 bedded Daycare Unit and a very busy out patient’s clinic.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The wider nursing team includes a Bone Marrow Transplant and Apheresis Team, Paediatric Oncology Outreach Team, Late Effects Service, Haemophilia and Benign Haematology Service as well as a thriving multi-disciplinary team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have completed your Preceptorship, developed clinical skills such as intravenous medication administration and demonstrate an interest in developing further clinical skills. You will need to have a positive and compassionate approach to caring for children and young people. You must have excellent communication skills, ability to work well under pressure, as part of a multi-disciplinary team and relate well to others.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For further details please contact&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Hilary Quinton (Lead Cancer Nurse)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;h.quinton@nhs.net&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
